race.comment: MIDNIGHT IN MINORI (8) has been knocking on the door of a maiden win in recent starts, finishing L away at Wodonga most recently. McDougall sticks from that effort and she has the speed to get into a handy spot from a tricky gate. Can land the knockout blow this time. ORGANICS (11) was sound first-up at Cranbourne when ending up near the tail of the line and closing off steadily. Coffey rides now and the extra trip looks a bonus, as does the easier grade. Expecting improvement out of her now. ICED POPPY (7) flew home at Gundagai last start with the apprentice on board in an eye-catching performance. Needs to sit a touch closer this time, and if she can, she'll be hard to hold out. LEFT ON READ (1) is third-up here and can improve again to be in the finish.
